# 1CommandAI — Cursor rules (platform monorepo)

You are building **1CommandAI** on **github.com/1commandai/platform**.

## Repository layout

- **frontend/** — Lovable prototype export (React UI). In this clone, UI may live at **src/** until migrated.
- **backend/** — Express + TypeScript API (Cursor-built). Modules under `backend/src/modules/`.
- **shared/types/** — Shared API contracts (`User`, `Agent`, `TenantRole`). **Do not duplicate** — import from `@shared/types/api` or `shared/types/api.ts`.
- **shared/openapi/** — Generated OpenAPI JSON (`npm run openapi:export`). Spec source: `@openapi` JSDoc in backend routes.

## When building backend APIs

1. Read the **frontend component** that will consume the endpoint (`src/components/*.tsx` or `frontend/src/components/`).
2. Match request/response shapes to **shared/types/api.ts**; extend shared types if the contract changes.
3. Add **Zod** validation (`*.validation.ts`) and **@openapi** JSDoc on routes/controllers.
4. **org_id from JWT only** — never trust tenant id from request body on authenticated routes.
5. After route changes: `npm run openapi:export` and `npm run openapi:types`.

## References

- Architecture: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `.cursor/rules/SYSTEM-PROMPT.mdc`
- API contract: `docs/API-CONTRACT.md`
- Cursor + Lovable: `docs/CURSOR-INTEGRATION.md`
- OpenAPI UI: `GET /api/docs` (backend running)

## Code standards

- TypeScript strict, no `any`
- Backend: InversifyJS, feature modules, `@modules/*` `@common/*` `@config/*`
- Frontend: Redux Toolkit + RTK Query, Tailwind + Shadcn, Vite
